Pre-heat your #oven to 200 degrees. Scrub the @sweet potato{1} under water and chop into bite-sized (2cm) chunks (without peeling).

Toss the chunks in 1 tbsp of @olive oil{1%tbsp} and season well with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Roast on the top shelf of your #oven for around ~{25%minutes}, or until soft enough to eat.

Peel the @beetroot{2} and chop into 2cm cubes, place in a #bowl. Toss in @olive oil{2%tsp} and season with a little pinch of @salt{} and @black pepper{}. When the sweet potato has been cooking for ~{5%minutes}, add the beetroot to the #baking tray{} to cook with the sweet potato for the remaining ~{20%minutes}.

> Rub a drop of olive oil into your fingers whilst handling the beetroot to stop stained fingers!

12 mins after the beetroot went into the oven, add the @chorizo{1}(diced) to the #baking tray{} to cook for the final ~{8%minutes}. Meanwhile, thinly slice the @spring onions{2}.

Once your sweet potato, beetroot and chorizo is cooked, remove them from your #oven and allow it to cool for ~{5%minutes}.

> Allowing it to cool slightly will prevent the salad leaves from wilting in the next step.

When cool, toss the mixture into the @mixed salad{1} together with the spring onions. Drizzle over the @Argentinian chimichurri dressing{1} and gently combine. Lastly crumble over the @goat's cheese{1/2} and enjoy!

> This dressing can be quite spicy, so if you don't like it hot, simply add half and add a splash of olive oil to the salad too.